name: Noble
bio:
Noble 'K9' Ezeh made his music industry debut in 2012 with the self-produced Afrobeat hit 'Kokoma' while signed to Trybe Records, a leading Nigerian label at the time, founded by Nigerian music industry icon Olanrewaju 'eLDeeTheDon' Dabiri.

After parting ways with Trybe Records, he quickly followed up in 2014 with his sophomore release, the self-produced street-hop anthem 'Lord Have Mercy', featuring Nigerian hip-hop heavyweight Olamide Baddo.

Since then, K9 has released 17 singles, including fan-favourites like:
- Oyi'm
- Akorda (Gimme Dat)
- Shey Yu Fit Pay

In 2022, he released his first body of work, the EP 'Nostalgia', which featured standout tracks like:
- Wassup
- Party & BS
- Steal Ur Luv

Expanding his artistry, Noble 'K9' Ezeh is also widely recognized for creating iconic jingles for major brands across Africa. Some of his most notable works include:
- The official theme song for Big Brother Naija—Africa’s biggest reality TV show. This groundbreaking song has been used in every season of the show since its resurgence in 2017.
- DStv's official anthem for the FIFA World Cup in Qatar.
- MTN's mPulse jingle, crafted for the telecom giant’s teen-focused product.

A modern-day Renaissance man, K9 is not only a music producer, singer, songwriter, and audio engineer but also holds a degree in French Language, is a certified banker from the Access Bank School of Banking Excellence, and a consummate business professional.
